'''Weeraketiya''' is a small town in [[Hambantota District]], Southern Province in southern [[Sri Lanka]]. It is known for being the birthplace of [[Mahinda Rajapaksa]].<ref name="Inc.2011">{{cite book|title=Britannica Book of the Year 2011|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=mfecAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA106|date=1 March 2011|publisher=Encyclopaedia Britannica, Inc.|isbn=978-1-61535-500-6|page=106}}</ref> The town belongs to [[Weeraketiya Divisional Secretariat]].

==History==
The St. Joseph's Estate operated in Weeraketiya in colonial times and produced tomatoes and coconuts.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Tropical Agriculturalist|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=QQtZAAAAYAAJ|year=1931|page=65}}</ref> In 1969 the Germans funded the installation of medium-wave 50 kilowatt transmitters at [[Maho]] and Weeraketiya.<ref name="Wilson2010">{{cite book|last=Wilson|first=A. Jeyaratnam|title=Electoral Politics in an Emergent State: The Ceylon General Election of May 1970|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Hj22Puk37IUC&pg=PA158|date=10 June 2010|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-15311-9|page=158}}</ref> It was installed by the first quarter of 1970.<ref>{{cite book|title=Ceylon Year Book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TeA-AQAAIAAJ|year=1971|publisher=Department of Census and Statistics.|page=339}}</ref>
In April 2009, a pastor in Weeraketiya was harassed and threatened by four people, leading to the arrest of one individual.<ref name="Leo">{{cite book|last=Leo|first=Leonard|title=International Religious Freedom (2010): Annual Report to Congress|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=eYSA2uew3CUC&pg=PA332|publisher=DIANE Publishing|isbn=978-1-4379-4439-6|page=332}}</ref>

==Landmarks==
The town lies around the Udakiriwila Tank (lake). The Seegala Temple of Pillars lies near its western bank. The town contains the [[Rajapaksha Central College]] and a National Youth Corps Training Center. To the south of the tank is [[Weeraketiya Hospital]], Singhapura Mithrathwa National School and the Teacher Training Center and Weerakatiya Rajapaksha Central College.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=Weeraketiya&ie=UTF-8&hq=&hnear=0x3ae14d9cc8d7b9d1:0x3b5f4eee7007e8df,Weeraketiya,+Sri+Lanka&gl=uk&ei=hZijUrCeN-qp7Aa09ICwCw&ved=0CHUQtgMwDQ|title=Weeraketiya|publisher=Google Maps|accessdate=7 December 2013}}</ref>

